From: Matthew Vick <matthew.vick@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 13 Dec 2012 07:20:37 +0000
Subject: [PATCH v5 013/164] igb: Free any held skb that should have been timestamped on
 remove

Git-commit: badc26dd648cb3017affb834e9f79995e3911335
Patch-mainline: v3.9-rc1
Reference: fate#317388, bsc#909491
Target: sle11-sp4

To prevent a race condition where an skb has been saved to return the Tx
timestamp later and the driver is removed, add a check to determine if we
have an skb stored and, if so, free it.

Cc: Richard Cochran <richardcochran@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Matthew Vick <matthew.vick@intel.com>
Acked-by: Jacob Keller <Jacob.e.keller@intel.com>
Tested-by: Aaron Brown <aaron.f.brown@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Acked-by: Lee, Chun-Yi <jlee@suse.com>

---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igb/igb_ptp.c |    4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

Index: linux-3.0-SLE11-SP4/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igb/igb_ptp.c
===================================================================
--- linux-3.0-SLE11-SP4.orig/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igb/igb_ptp.c
+++ linux-3.0-SLE11-SP4/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igb/igb_ptp.c
@@ -856,6 +856,10 @@ void igb_ptp_stop(struct igb_adapter *ad
 	}
 
 	cancel_work_sync(&adapter->ptp_tx_work);
+	if (adapter->ptp_tx_skb) {
+		dev_kfree_skb_any(adapter->ptp_tx_skb);
+		adapter->ptp_tx_skb = NULL;
+	}
 
 	if (adapter->ptp_clock) {
 		ptp_clock_unregister(adapter->ptp_clock);
